Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.73,0:00:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.83,0:00:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,something very colorful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 and Wide Gamut, what
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that is and how we use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But first I want to mention
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,color management real quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.66,0:00:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,With color management we make
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.96,0:00:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that the display colors as
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.51,0:00:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,accurately as possible across
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,devices, platforms, and color
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.21,0:00:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,spaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.58,0:00:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And color management is built
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.23,0:00:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,into both Mac OS and iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.61,0:00:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And color management helps avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.61,0:00:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a situation like this where
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.29,0:00:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,colors are incorrectly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.71,0:00:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,represented going from source to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.97,0:01:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.90,0:01:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So as a designer makes sure to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.79,0:01:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,tag your assets properly to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.91,0:01:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,allow for color management to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.69,0:01:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,accurately display your colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.88,0:01:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is then Display P3?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.26,0:01:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Very simply put it's a color
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.65,0:01:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,space within the RGB color model
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.11,0:01:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that represents a larger
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.34,0:01:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,spectrum of colors than the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.97,0:01:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,current industry standard sRGB.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.17,0:01:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of us have been using
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.82,0:01:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sRGB for probably over a decade
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.50,0:01:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,now, but with display P3 we get
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.55,0:01:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a 25 percent larger color space
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.35,0:01:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to sRGB.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.17,0:01:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that they can
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.66,0:01:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,represent more colors with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.66,0:01:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,better accuracy and stay more
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.08,0:01:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,true to what those colors
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.79,0:01:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,actually look like in real life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.31,0:01:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this image the black
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.98,0:01:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,strobe represents the size of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.79,0:01:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the sRGB color space and as you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,can see the Display P3 extends
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,way beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.53,0:01:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the color space is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.94,0:01:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,larger than sRGB it is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.46,0:02:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,informally referred to as a wide
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.70,0:02:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,gamut color space, also displays
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,supporting a larger color space
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.52,0:02:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,than sRGB referred to as wide
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.61,0:02:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,gamut displays.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.55,0:02:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the late 2015 iMac Retina
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.71,0:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was the first consumer-facing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.12,0:02:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,computer that supported Display
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.75,0:02:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,P3.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.05,0:02:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When working with the Display P3
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.51,0:02:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,color profile you have the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.15,0:02:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity to also use a larger
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.62,0:02:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,color depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.80,0:02:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,16 bit per channel instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.59,0:02:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the usual 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.22,0:02:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That allows you to represent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.62,0:02:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,more colors within the wide
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.99,0:02:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,gamut, which is especially
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.68,0:02:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,useful for gradients.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.65,0:02:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at an
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.60,0:02:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,example of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.10,0:02:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is a somewhat
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.03,0:02:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,exaggerated example, but clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.76,0:02:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we have banding happening in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.91,0:02:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this sRGB gradient.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.45,0:02:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Something i could try to get run
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by using dithering.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.06,0:02:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will look something like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.08,0:02:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.95,0:02:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if I instead use Display
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,P3and set my color depth to 16
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.08,0:02:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,bits per channel, then banding
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.79,0:02:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is then much less visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.61,0:03:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're simply closing the gap
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,between each defined color,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,giving us a much better result.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.59,0:03:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we chose to display P3 for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.70,0:03:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,its similarities to our existing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.40,0:03:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,view and conditions that were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,already defined in sRGB.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.70,0:03:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then by lining both the gamut
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.44,0:03:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the wide points, we get a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.02,0:03:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,color space that behaves very
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.49,0:03:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,similar, making the threshold to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.99,0:03:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,understand again working with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.67,0:03:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 much lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.50,0:03:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we move on I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.01,0:03:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,mention that since we're looking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.19,0:03:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,at this presentation on sRGB
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,based projection system, all of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.25,0:03:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the examples in this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.29,0:03:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation are renditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.68,0:03:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which then leads me to who can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,actually see Display P3 Images?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.17,0:03:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well users needs a wide gamut
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,display that supports the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.67,0:03:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 color space and color
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.78,0:03:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.79,0:03:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And Apple has supported wide
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.06,0:03:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,gamut displays since the late
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.72,0:03:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,2015 iMac Retina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.83,0:03:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But now there's a wider range of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.34,0:04:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,devices that all support Display
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,P3 -- for example, the iPhone 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.35,0:04:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the MacBook Pro with a Touch Bar
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.02,0:04:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and also the iPad Pro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about you as a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,designer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.42,0:04:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you do not want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.65,0:04:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,flying blind when creating
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.67,0:04:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.16,0:04:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You want full control over your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.83,0:04:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.20,0:04:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So make sure to work on a wide
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,gamut display that supports
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.32,0:04:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 like the MacBook Pro
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.17,0:04:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Touch Bar, the iMac
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.43,0:04:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Retina, or the LG5K Display.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.59,0:04:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we know what display P3
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.60,0:04:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is and how we can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.12,0:04:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.89,0:04:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In this beautiful image we have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.22,0:04:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,some really nice colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.43,0:04:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Some with wide ranges of red,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.37,0:04:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,green, and orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.83,0:04:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is an sRGB image to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.68,0:04:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,current standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.45,0:04:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But because of the limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.31,0:04:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,within sRGB, not all colors that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.98,0:04:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,were captured by the camera are
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.73,0:04:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in this photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Represented here by these light
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:04:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,blue fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply because these colors were
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.71,0:05:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,not available in the sRGB color
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.89,0:05:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The display P3 version of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,same image is a completely
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.52,0:05:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have rich, beautiful, and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,bold colors throughout the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,entire image.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.24,0:05:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you compare the three
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.46,0:05:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,images we have a pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.96,0:05:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,significant difference and I
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.79,0:05:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,almost feel a little bit sad for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.44,0:05:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,out buddy here on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks really bad right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, so let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.74,0:05:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 Workflow and we're
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.25,0:05:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be using Photoshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.73,0:05:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's begin with a brand new
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,document, and in order to take
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,full advantage of all of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,colors available in the Display
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.67,0:05:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,P3 Color Space, the first thing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to do is to tag your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.14,0:05:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,asset with the correct color
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.67,0:05:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm creating that new
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.39,0:05:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,document in Photoshop, make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.25,0:05:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to set your color profile to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing I want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.10,0:05:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is to change the color depth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.91,0:06:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,from 8 to 16 bits per channel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.41,0:06:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.46,0:06:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you're finished with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.59,0:06:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you're absolutely fantastic
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.27,0:06:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,design, it is now time to save
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.30,0:06:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,out your artwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are multiple ways of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.80,0:06:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,doing so on Photoshop like using
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.77,0:06:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Generator or Export As.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.05,0:06:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But in this case it is key then
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.55,0:06:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to use Save As and PNG as your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.00,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,format because this is the only
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,way at the moment to both imbed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a color profile and maintain the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,color depth without -- in the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,exported asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.30,0:06:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Generator will not
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.72,0:06:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,imbed a color profile and leave
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.05,0:06:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,your asset entirely untagged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So only use Save As.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.01,0:06:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When opening raw files in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.11,0:06:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Photoshop, make sure to tag --
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.40,0:06:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to change the color profile to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,display P3 and the color depth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.29,0:06:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to 16 bits per channel by
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.10,0:06:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,clicking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.42,0:06:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, if you're receiving assets
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.83,0:07:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from someone else, makes sure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.20,0:07:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that those assets are converted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.61,0:07:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to display P3 directly from the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,raw file and not sRGB as the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.58,0:07:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,color information would then
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.93,0:07:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,already be completely lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.16,0:07:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So walk down your asset pipeline
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and make sure you get Display P3
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,assets directly from your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.84,0:07:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,source.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.81,0:07:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're working from an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,existing asset like an app icon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure to use Convert to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This will actually perform a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,color match operation and not
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.83,0:07:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,alter your design.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.38,0:07:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Click like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.73,0:07:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And do not use Assign to Profile
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.33,0:07:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as that will take your existing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.78,0:07:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,colors and stretch those out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.34,0:07:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,into the new color space
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.09,0:07:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,changing your design in some
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.89,0:07:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.59,0:07:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So always use Convert to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.87,0:07:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.48,0:07:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example let's look what
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.20,0:07:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,happens to the RGB of values
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,before and after converting to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.21,0:07:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,display P3 from an sRGB
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.93,0:07:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Gradient.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:08:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,red color spefically here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.99,0:08:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in this sRGB image you can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.41,0:08:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,see that I'll all the way up in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the top right corner and our RGB
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,values are then 255, 0, 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.39,0:08:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty much as red as it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.83,0:08:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.20,0:08:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But after converting to display
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.71,0:08:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,P3 I can now see that I have a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.84,0:08:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,lot more red to work with and I
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can also see that my RGB values
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.40,0:08:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,has now changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.68,0:08:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you guys are now ready to go
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.32,0:08:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and create stunning Display P3
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.47,0:08:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Assets for your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But before you do take a second
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask the question, should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.23,0:08:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 works great in some
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.08,0:08:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,cases, in others it's just not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.43,0:08:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the right choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.69,0:08:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,designed with a calm,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.70,0:08:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,de-saturated color scheme, it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.60,0:08:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't use a lot of imagery,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.19,0:08:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,display P3 might not be the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,right choice for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.70,0:08:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is great for calling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,attention to certain details
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.47,0:08:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,within your UI, such like a VU
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.52,0:08:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,meter or the red line in the rev
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:08:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,counter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or used to smooth out that app
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.98,0:09:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,icon gradient.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.13,0:09:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if your app uses a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.12,0:09:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,scenic imagery of nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.30,0:09:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,landscapes, or travel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.31,0:09:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,destinations, this use of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 makes a whole lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.93,0:09:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sense because these images will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.81,0:09:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,look more vibrant and richer and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.91,0:09:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,colors will stay more true to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.75,0:09:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what they actually looked like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.27,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when the camera captured that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.63,0:09:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,very specific and special image.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.86,0:09:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Or for apps that feature
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.01,0:09:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,textiles or garments were shown
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.89,0:09:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the true color of a dress or a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pair of pants is immensely
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,important.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So in conclusion, we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.58,0:09:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Display P3 color space and color
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.83,0:09:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,profile.
